      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span> Setup Git repository</h3>
      <ul class="bigboy">
        <li>Create the Git repo on your local machine, install and run locally.</li>
        <code>
          $ git clone https://github.com/mlaurel/dbc-shuffle.git <br>
          $ cd dbc-shuffle <br>
          $ bundle exec rake db:create db:migrate <br>
          $ bundle exec rails s <br>
        </code>
      </ul>

      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span> Set Heroku remote for existing Git repository</h3>
      <ul class="bigboy">
        <li>For existing repositories, simply add the heroku remote</li>
        <code>
          $ heroku login <br>
          $ heroku git:remote -a dbc-shuffle <br>
        </code>
      </ul>

      <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span> Run Application Locally</h3>
      <ul class="bigboy">
        <li>To run the app locally, you can use the heroku local</li>
        <code>
          $ bundle install <br>
          $ rails s <br>
        </code>
